            "year": "2029",
            "text": "Reserves"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "year": "2029",
            "text": "\"Reserves\" are collections resources that we have identified within the Earth that we can extract at some point—but haven't yet. Estimates relating to reserves fluctuate as economic forces, technological chanages, and new resource discoveries alter what we know about resource availability and extraction feasibility. Nevertheless, they are most certainly <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abundance_of_elements_in_Earth%27s_crust\">finite</a>."
        },
